## 🔄 Application Workflow

### 1. User Registration Flow

```
User fills registration form (Name, Email, Password)
        ↓
Frontend sends POST request to /api/register
        ↓
Backend validates input
        ↓
Password is hashed using bcrypt
        ↓
User credentials stored in MySQL
        ↓
User profile created in MongoDB
        ↓
Success response sent to frontend
        ↓
User redirected to login page
```

### 2. User Login Flow

```
User enters email and password
        ↓
Frontend sends POST request to /api/login
        ↓
Backend validates credentials from MySQL
        ↓
Password verified using bcrypt
        ↓
Session created and stored in Redis
        ↓
Session token sent to frontend
        ↓
User redirected to profile page
```

### 3. Profile Management Flow

```
User accesses profile page
        ↓
Session token validated via Redis
        ↓
User can view/update profile (Age, DOB, Contact)
        ↓
Frontend sends POST request to /api/profile/update
        ↓
Profile data updated in MongoDB
        ↓
User can view details by clicking "See Details"
        ↓
User can logout (session cleared from Redis)
```

---

## 🌐 API Endpoints

### Authentication Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/register` | Register new user |
| POST | `/api/login` | User login |

### Profile Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/profile/update` | Update user profile |
| GET | `/api/profile/details` | Get user profile details |
| POST | `/api/logout` | User logout |

